    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the pottery found in central Anatolia from about 2400 to 2000 BCE. The style is characterized by vessels decorated with painted pink to brown geometric motifs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica encontrado en Anatolia Central desde alrededor del 2400 al 2000 a.C. El estilo se caracteriza por vasijas decoradas con motivos geométricos pintados de rosa a café.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar het aardwerk uit circa 2400 tot 2000 v. Chr. dat in het midden van Anatolië werd gevonden. De stijl kenmerkt zich door vazen die werden beschilderd met roze tot bruine geometrische motieven.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
